 159     def test_constructor_mixed_dtypes(self):
 160         def _make_mixed_dtypes_df(typ, ad=None):
 161 
 162             if typ == "int":
 163                 dtypes = MIXED_INT_DTYPES
 164                 arrays = [np.array(np.random.rand(10), dtype=d) for d in dtypes]
 165             elif typ == "float":
 166                 dtypes = MIXED_FLOAT_DTYPES
 167                 arrays = [
 168                     np.array(np.random.randint(10, size=10), dtype=d) for d in dtypes
 169                 ]
 170 
 171             for d, a in zip(dtypes, arrays):
 172                 assert a.dtype == d
 173             if ad is None:
 174                 ad = dict()
 175             ad.update({d: a for d, a in zip(dtypes, arrays)})
 176             return DataFrame(ad)
 177 
 178         def _check_mixed_dtypes(df, dtypes=None):
 179             if dtypes is None:
 180                 dtypes = MIXED_FLOAT_DTYPES + MIXED_INT_DTYPES
 181             for d in dtypes:
 182                 if d in df:
 183                     assert df.dtypes[d] == d
 184 
 185         # mixed floating and integer coexist in the same frame
 186         df = _make_mixed_dtypes_df("float")
 187         _check_mixed_dtypes(df)
 188 
 189         # add lots of types
 190         df = _make_mixed_dtypes_df("float", dict(A=1, B="foo", C="bar"))
 191         _check_mixed_dtypes(df)
 192 
 193         # GH 622
 194         df = _make_mixed_dtypes_df("int")
 195         _check_mixed_dtypes(df)

 217     def test_constructor_rec(self, float_frame):

 220

 240         # see gh-14881

 289     def test_constructor_dict(self):
 290         datetime_series = tm.makeTimeSeries(nper=30)
 291         # test expects index shifted by 5
 292         datetime_series_short = tm.makeTimeSeries(nper=30)[5:]
 293 
 294         frame = DataFrame({"col1": datetime_series, "col2": datetime_series_short})
 295 
 296         # col2 is padded with NaN
 297         assert len(datetime_series) == 30
 298         assert len(datetime_series_short) == 25
 299 
 300         tm.assert_series_equal(frame["col1"], datetime_series.rename("col1"))
 301 
 302         exp = Series(
 303             np.concatenate([[np.nan] * 5, datetime_series_short.values]),
 304             index=datetime_series.index,
 305             name="col2",
 306         )
 307         tm.assert_series_equal(exp, frame["col2"])
 308 
 309         frame = DataFrame(
 310             {"col1": datetime_series, "col2": datetime_series_short},
 311             columns=["col2", "col3", "col4"],
 312         )
 313 
 314         assert len(frame) == len(datetime_series_short)
 315         assert "col1" not in frame
 316         assert isna(frame["col3"]).all()
 317 
 318         # Corner cases
 319         assert len(DataFrame()) == 0
 320 
 321         # mix dict and array, wrong size - no spec for which error should raise
 322         # first
 323         msg = "Mixing dicts with non-Series may lead to ambiguous ordering."
 324         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=msg):
 325             DataFrame({"A": {"a": "a", "b": "b"}, "B": ["a", "b", "c"]})
 326 
 327         # Length-one dict micro-optimization
 328         frame = DataFrame({"A": {"1": 1, "2": 2}})
 329         tm.assert_index_equal(frame.index, Index(["1", "2"]))
 330 
 331         # empty dict plus index
 332         idx = Index([0, 1, 2])
 333         frame = DataFrame({}, index=idx)
 334         assert frame.index is idx
 335 
 336         # empty dict with index and columns
 337         idx = Index([0, 1, 2])
 338         frame = DataFrame({}, index=idx, columns=idx)
 339         assert frame.index is idx
 340         assert frame.columns is idx
 341         assert len(frame._series) == 3
 342 
 343         # with dict of empty list and Series
 344         frame = DataFrame({"A": [], "B": []}, columns=["A", "B"])
 345         tm.assert_index_equal(frame.index, Index([], dtype=np.int64))
 346 
 347         # GH 14381
 348         # Dict with None value
 349         frame_none = DataFrame(dict(a=None), index=[0])
 350         frame_none_list = DataFrame(dict(a=[None]), index=[0])
 351         assert frame_none._get_value(0, "a") is None
 352         assert frame_none_list._get_value(0, "a") is None
 353         tm.assert_frame_equal(frame_none, frame_none_list)
 354 
 355         # GH10856
 356         # dict with scalar values should raise error, even if columns passed
 357         msg = "If using all scalar values, you must pass an index"
 358         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=msg):
 359             DataFrame({"a": 0.7})
 360 
 361         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=msg):
 362             DataFrame({"a": 0.7}, columns=["a"])
 363

 623     def test_constructor_dict_multiindex(self):
 624         def check(result, expected):
 625             return tm.assert_frame_equal(
 626                 result,
 627                 expected,
 628                 check_dtype=True,
 629                 check_index_type=True,
 630                 check_column_type=True,
 631                 check_names=True,
 632             )
 633 
 634         d = {
 635             ("a", "a"): {("i", "i"): 0, ("i", "j"): 1, ("j", "i"): 2},
 636             ("b", "a"): {("i", "i"): 6, ("i", "j"): 5, ("j", "i"): 4},
 637             ("b", "c"): {("i", "i"): 7, ("i", "j"): 8, ("j", "i"): 9},
 638         }
 639         _d = sorted(d.items())
 640         df = DataFrame(d)
 641         expected = DataFrame(
 642             [x[1] for x in _d], index=MultiIndex.from_tuples([x[0] for x in _d])
 643         ).T
 644         expected.index = MultiIndex.from_tuples(expected.index)
 645         check(df, expected)
 646 
 647         d["z"] = {"y": 123.0, ("i", "i"): 111, ("i", "j"): 111, ("j", "i"): 111}
 648         _d.insert(0, ("z", d["z"]))
 649         expected = DataFrame(
 650             [x[1] for x in _d], index=Index([x[0] for x in _d], tupleize_cols=False)
 651         ).T
 652         expected.index = Index(expected.index, tupleize_cols=False)
 653         df = DataFrame(d)
 654         df = df.reindex(columns=expected.columns, index=expected.index)
 655         check(df, expected)

 746     def _check_basic_constructor(self, empty):
 747         # mat: 2d matrix with shape (3, 2) to input. empty - makes sized
 748         # objects
 749         mat = empty((2, 3), dtype=float)
 750         # 2-D input
 751         frame = DataFrame(mat, columns=["A", "B", "C"], index=[1, 2])
 752 
 753         assert len(frame.index) == 2
 754         assert len(frame.columns) == 3
 755 
 756         # 1-D input
 757         frame = DataFrame(empty((3,)), columns=["A"], index=[1, 2, 3])
 758         assert len(frame.index) == 3
 759         assert len(frame.columns) == 1
 760 
 761         # cast type
 762         frame = DataFrame(mat, columns=["A", "B", "C"], index=[1, 2], dtype=np.int64)
 763         assert frame.values.dtype == np.int64
 764 
 765         # wrong size axis labels
 766         msg = r"Shape of passed values is \(2, 3\), indices imply \(1, 3\)"
 767         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=msg):
 768             DataFrame(mat, columns=["A", "B", "C"], index=[1])
 769         msg = r"Shape of passed values is \(2, 3\), indices imply \(2, 2\)"
 770         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=msg):
 771             DataFrame(mat, columns=["A", "B"], index=[1, 2])
 772 
 773         # higher dim raise exception
 774         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match="Must pass 2-d input"):
 775             DataFrame(empty((3, 3, 3)), columns=["A", "B", "C"], index=[1])
 776 
 777         # automatic labeling
 778         frame = DataFrame(mat)
 779         tm.assert_index_equal(frame.index, pd.Int64Index(range(2)))
 780         tm.assert_index_equal(frame.columns, pd.Int64Index(range(3)))
 781 
 782         frame = DataFrame(mat, index=[1, 2])
 783         tm.assert_index_equal(frame.columns, pd.Int64Index(range(3)))
 784 
 785         frame = DataFrame(mat, columns=["A", "B", "C"])
 786         tm.assert_index_equal(frame.index, pd.Int64Index(range(2)))
 787 
 788         # 0-length axis
 789         frame = DataFrame(empty((0, 3)))
 790         assert len(frame.index) == 0
 791 
 792         frame = DataFrame(empty((3, 0)))
 793         assert len(frame.columns) == 0

 913     def test_constructor_mrecarray(self):
 914         # Ensure mrecarray produces frame identical to dict of masked arrays
 915         # from GH3479
 916 
 917         assert_fr_equal = functools.partial(
 918             tm.assert_frame_equal, check_index_type=True, check_column_type=True,
 919         )
 920         arrays = [
 921             ("float", np.array([1.5, 2.0])),
 922             ("int", np.array([1, 2])),
 923             ("str", np.array(["abc", "def"])),
 924         ]
 925         for name, arr in arrays[:]:
 926             arrays.append(
 927                 ("masked1_" + name, np.ma.masked_array(arr, mask=[False, True]))
 928             )
 929         arrays.append(("masked_all", np.ma.masked_all((2,))))
 930         arrays.append(("masked_none", np.ma.masked_array([1.0, 2.5], mask=False)))
 931 
 932         # call assert_frame_equal for all selections of 3 arrays
 933         for comb in itertools.combinations(arrays, 3):
 934             names, data = zip(*comb)
 935             mrecs = mrecords.fromarrays(data, names=names)
 936 
 937             # fill the comb
 938             comb = {k: (v.filled() if hasattr(v, "filled") else v) for k, v in comb}
 939 
 940             expected = DataFrame(comb, columns=names)
 941             result = DataFrame(mrecs)
 942             assert_fr_equal(result, expected)
 943 
 944             # specify columns
 945             expected = DataFrame(comb, columns=names[::-1])
 946             result = DataFrame(mrecs, columns=names[::-1])
 947             assert_fr_equal(result, expected)
 948 
 949             # specify index
 950             expected = DataFrame(comb, columns=names, index=[1, 2])
 951             result = DataFrame(mrecs, index=[1, 2])
 952             assert_fr_equal(result, expected)

2277     def test_from_records_sequencelike(self):
2278         df = DataFrame(
2279             {
2280                 "A": np.array(np.random.randn(6), dtype=np.float64),
2281                 "A1": np.array(np.random.randn(6), dtype=np.float64),
2282                 "B": np.array(np.arange(6), dtype=np.int64),
2283                 "C": ["foo"] * 6,
2284                 "D": np.array([True, False] * 3, dtype=bool),
2285                 "E": np.array(np.random.randn(6), dtype=np.float32),
2286                 "E1": np.array(np.random.randn(6), dtype=np.float32),
2287                 "F": np.array(np.arange(6), dtype=np.int32),
2288             }
2289         )
2290 
2291         # this is actually tricky to create the recordlike arrays and
2292         # have the dtypes be intact
2293         blocks = df._to_dict_of_blocks()
2294         tuples = []
2295         columns = []
2296         dtypes = []
2297         for dtype, b in blocks.items():
2298             columns.extend(b.columns)
2299             dtypes.extend([(c, np.dtype(dtype).descr[0][1]) for c in b.columns])
2300         for i in range(len(df.index)):
2301             tup = []
2302             for _, b in blocks.items():
2303                 tup.extend(b.iloc[i].values)
2304             tuples.append(tuple(tup))
2305 
2306         recarray = np.array(tuples, dtype=dtypes).view(np.recarray)
2307         recarray2 = df.to_records()
2308         lists = [list(x) for x in tuples]
2309 
2310         # tuples (lose the dtype info)
2311         result = DataFrame.from_records(tuples, columns=columns).reindex(
2312             columns=df.columns
2313         )
2314 
2315         # created recarray and with to_records recarray (have dtype info)
2316         result2 = DataFrame.from_records(recarray, columns=columns).reindex(
2317             columns=df.columns
2318         )
2319         result3 = DataFrame.from_records(recarray2, columns=columns).reindex(
2320             columns=df.columns
2321         )
2322 
2323         # list of tupels (no dtype info)
2324         result4 = DataFrame.from_records(lists, columns=columns).reindex(
2325             columns=df.columns
2326         )
2327 
2328         tm.assert_frame_equal(result, df, check_dtype=False)
2329         tm.assert_frame_equal(result2, df)
2330         tm.assert_frame_equal(result3, df)
2331         tm.assert_frame_equal(result4, df, check_dtype=False)
2332 
2333         # tuples is in the order of the columns
2334         result = DataFrame.from_records(tuples)
2335         tm.assert_index_equal(result.columns, pd.RangeIndex(8))
2336 
2337         # test exclude parameter & we are casting the results here (as we don't
2338         # have dtype info to recover)
2339         columns_to_test = [columns.index("C"), columns.index("E1")]
2340 
2341         exclude = list(set(range(8)) - set(columns_to_test))
2342         result = DataFrame.from_records(tuples, exclude=exclude)
2343         result.columns = [columns[i] for i in sorted(columns_to_test)]
2344         tm.assert_series_equal(result["C"], df["C"])
2345         tm.assert_series_equal(result["E1"], df["E1"].astype("float64"))
2346 
2347         # empty case
2348         result = DataFrame.from_records([], columns=["foo", "bar", "baz"])
2349         assert len(result) == 0
2350         tm.assert_index_equal(result.columns, Index(["foo", "bar", "baz"]))
2351 
2352         result = DataFrame.from_records([])
2353         assert len(result) == 0
2354         assert len(result.columns) == 0
